require_dependency "action/admin/s3_storage"

module AwsGateway
  class GetStatementObject
    include Actionizer

    inputs_for(:call) do
      required :first_data_account_reference, type: String
      required :statement_date, type: Date
    end
    def call
      # This is a workaround to account for FDR's statement generation process.
      # If the account cycles on a Saturday or Sunday (non-processing day), they
      # will process it a day early/late. This results in the statement that we
      # receive to be named according to the earlier/later date.
      [0, -1, 1].each do |offset|
        key = object_key(input[:statement_date] + offset.day)
        s3_object = Action::S3Storage.object(key: key).object
        output[:s3_object] = s3_object
        break if s3_object.exists?
      end
    end

    private

    def object_key(statement_date)
      filename = "#{statement_date.strftime("%m%d%y")}.pdf"
      File.join(Env.aws_statements_path, input[:first_data_account_reference], filename)
    end
  end
end

require_dependency "persistence/persistence_base_v2"

describe PersistenceBaseV2 do
  subject { described_class.new }

  before do
    dummy_gateway = Class.new {
      cattr_accessor :dummy_object

      def self.delete!(_id)
      end

      def self.create!(*_params)
      end

      def self.find_or_create_by!(*_params)
      end

      def self.import(_value)
      end
    }
    stub_const("DummyGatewayV2", dummy_gateway)

    dummy_entity = Class.new(Hashie::Dash) {
      property :foo
    }
    stub_const("DummyEntityV2", dummy_entity)

    persistence_dummy = Class.new(PersistenceBaseV2) {
      def entity_class
        DummyEntityV2
      end

      def local_gateway_class
        DummyGatewayV2
      end

      def find
        cache(input[:id], expire_time: CentralTime.now.midnight + 3.hours) do
          serialize_output(Actionizer::Result.new(dummy_v2: DummyEntityV2.new(foo: "bar")))
        end
      end

      action def find_with_version
        cache(input[:id], version: input[:version]) do
          serialize_output(Actionizer::Result.new(dummy_v2: DummyEntityV2.new(foo: "version: #{input[:version]}")))
        end
      end

      def where
        cache(input[:id]) do
          serialize_array_output(Actionizer::Result.new(dummy_v2s: [DummyEntityV2.new(foo: "bar")]))
        end
      end
    }
    stub_const("Persistence::DummyV2", persistence_dummy)
  end

  context "cache" do
    let(:id) { SecureRandom.uuid }
    let(:s3_key) { "cache/v1/credit_card/persistence/dummy_v2/find/#{id}" }
    let(:last_modified) { current_time }
    let(:current_time) { CentralTime.now.midnight + 4.hours }

    before do
      travel_to current_time
      allow_any_instance_of(S3MockObject).to receive(:last_modified).and_return(last_modified)
      stub_env("CACHING_ENABLED" => "true")
      assume_existing_storage(key: s3_key, value: nil)
    end

    after { travel_back }

    it "successfully caches and retrieves find call" do
      result = Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)
      Action::S3Storage.get!(key: s3_key).value
      expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key, value: [:foo, "bar"])
      expect(CreditCardLogger).to receive(:info)
      cached_result = Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)

      expect(cached_result.value).not_to be_nil
      expect(cached_result.value).to eq(result.value)
      expect(result).to be_success
      expect(cached_result).to be_success
    end

    context "when s3_value is an array" do
      let(:id) { SecureRandom.uuid }
      let(:s3_key) { "cache/v1/credit_card/persistence/dummy_v2/where/#{id}" }

      it "successfully caches and retrieves where call" do
        result = Persistence::DummyV2.where(id: id)
        expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key, value: [{foo: "bar"}])
        cached_result = Persistence::DummyV2.where(id: id)

        expect(cached_result.value).not_to be_nil
        expect(cached_result.value).to eq(result.value)
        expect(result).to be_success
        expect(cached_result).to be_success
      end
    end

    context "cache_clear" do
      it "successfully clears the cache" do
        result = Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)
        expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key, value: [:foo, "bar"])
        Persistence::DummyV2.cache_clear(method_name: :find, cache_param: id)
        expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key, value: nil)

        expect(result).to be_success
      end

      context "when s3 fails" do
        before do
          allow(S3_BUCKET).to receive(:object).and_raise(StandardError)
        end

        it "logs error but succeeds" do
          expect(CreditCardLogger).to receive(:error)
          result = Persistence::DummyV2.cache_clear(method_name: :find, cache_param: id)

          expect(result).to be_success
        end
      end
    end

    context "when the cache is outdated" do
      let(:last_modified) { CentralTime.now.midnight + 2.hours }
      let(:current_time) { CentralTime.now.midnight + 4.hours }

      it "does not retrieve from cache" do
        expect(Action::S3Storage).to receive(:set!).and_call_original
        Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)
        expect(Action::S3Storage).to receive(:set!).and_call_original
        result = Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)

        expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key, value: [:foo, "bar"])
        expect(result).to be_success
      end
    end

    context "when #cache is called between midnight and 3 AM" do
      let(:current_time) { CentralTime.now.midnight + 1.hour }

      it "retrives from cache" do
        result = Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)
        Action::S3Storage.get!(key: s3_key).value
        expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key, value: [:foo, "bar"])
        expect(Action::S3Storage).not_to receive(:set!).and_call_original
        cached_result = Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)

        expect(cached_result.value).not_to be_nil
        expect(cached_result.value).to eq(result.value)
        expect(result).to be_success
        expect(cached_result).to be_success
      end
    end

    context "when #cache includes the :version parameter" do
      let(:s3_key_version_1) { "cache/v1/credit_card/persistence/dummy_v2/find_with_version/#{id}" }
      let(:s3_key_version_2) { "cache/v2/credit_card/persistence/dummy_v2/find_with_version/#{id}" }

      before do
        assume_existing_storage(key: s3_key_version_1, value: nil)
        assume_existing_storage(key: s3_key_version_2, value: nil)
      end

      it "retrieves a version-specific object from cache" do
        result_v1 = Persistence::DummyV2.find_with_version(id: id, version: 1)
        Action::S3Storage.get!(key: s3_key_version_1).value
        expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key_version_1, value: [:foo, "version: 1"])
        expect(CreditCardLogger).to receive(:info)
        cached_result_v1 = Persistence::DummyV2.find_with_version(id: id, version: 1)

        result_v2 = Persistence::DummyV2.find_with_version(id: id, version: 2)
        Action::S3Storage.get!(key: s3_key_version_2).value
        expect_successful_storage(key: s3_key_version_2, value: [:foo, "version: 2"])
        expect(CreditCardLogger).to receive(:info)
        cached_result_v2 = Persistence::DummyV2.find_with_version(id: id, version: 2)

        expect(cached_result_v1.value).not_to be_nil
        expect(cached_result_v2.value).not_to be_nil
        expect(cached_result_v1.value).to eq(result_v1.value)
        expect(cached_result_v2.value).to eq(result_v2.value)
        expect(result_v1.value).not_to eq(result_v2.value)
        expect(result_v1).to be_success
        expect(result_v2).to be_success
        expect(cached_result_v1).to be_success
        expect(cached_result_v2).to be_success
      end
    end

    context "when S3 fails" do
      before do
        allow(S3_BUCKET).to receive(:object).and_raise(StandardError)
      end

      it "logs error but succeeds" do
        expect(CreditCardLogger).to receive(:error)
        result = Persistence::DummyV2.find(id: id)

        expect(result).to be_success
      end
    end
  end
end
